# User Coding Standards

- Use TypeScript strict mode. Prefer explicit types at boundaries (API, DB, props).
- Validate external/input data (e.g. Zod) in server actions and API handlers.
- Prefer small, focused modules; one main concern per file.
- Prefer named exports for components and utilities.
- Centralize mapping between layers (e.g. DB snake_case → domain camelCase) in repos/services, not in UI.
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` and narrowing when types are uncertain.
- Handle errors explicitly: log and rethrow or return typed errors instead of swallowing.
